.swiftpm/
# Note: we intentionally do NOT ignore *.xcodeproj at repo level — the
# example app under Examples/ ships its xcodeproj so users can clone
# and run it without recreating the project. SPM-generated transient
# xcodeproj files live in DerivedData (already excluded) and never
# appear in the working tree.

# The example app's shared scheme can carry a `FEDDY_API_KEY`
# environment variable for local testing. Xcode persists scheme-level
# launch env vars only in the *shared* scheme (user schemes don't
# override them), so any contributor wiring a real Project ID for
# local runs would otherwise stage it for commit. Keep the example's
# shared schemes out of git entirely; Xcode auto-generates a working
# scheme on first open for new clones.
Examples/*/FeddyTestApp.xcodeproj/xcshareddata/xcschemes/

